<section class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1.4fr)_minmax(21rem,0.8fr)]">
  <div class="space-y-8">
    <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-3 rounded-md border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 px-4 py-2">
      <span class="h-2 w-2 rounded-full bg-emerald-500 shadow-[0_0_8px_rgba(34,197,94,0.5)]"></span>
      <span class="text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-slate-500" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Local Engine Sandbox</span>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-5">
      <p class="max-w-xl text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.34em] text-slate-600" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">
        Mount. Seed. Break. Improve.
      </p>
      <h1 class="max-w-3xl text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100 sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; letter-spacing: -0.03em;">
        Test the engine in a real Rails app.
      </h1>
      <p class="max-w-2xl text-base leading-7 text-slate-400">
        This host app exists to validate whether CompletionKit works when mounted for real. It seeds a prompt, a CSV-backed run, and gives you a clean launch surface into the engine.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
      <%= link_to "Launch Engine UI", "/completion_kit", class: "inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-cyan-400 px-5 py-2.5 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-[#080b14] shadow-lg shadow-cyan-400/20 transition hover:-translate-y-0.5 hover:bg-cyan-300 hover:shadow-cyan-400/30", style: "font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;" %>
      <%= link_to "Prompts", "/completion_kit/prompts", class: "inline-flex items-center rounded-md border border-slate-700 px-5 py-2.5 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400 transition hover:border-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-400", style: "font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;" %>
      <%= link_to "Runs", "/completion_kit/test_runs", class: "inline-flex items-center rounded-md border border-slate-700 px-5 py-2.5 text-xs font-medium uppercase tracking-wider text-slate-400 transition hover:border-cyan-400 hover:text-cyan-400", style: "font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;" %>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-3 md:grid-cols-3">
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-5">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-slate-600" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Seeded Prompts</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-cyan-400" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;"><%= @prompt_count %></p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-5">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-slate-600" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Seeded Test Runs</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-cyan-400" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;"><%= @test_run_count %></p>
      </div>
      <div class="rounded-lg border border-cyan-900/50 bg-gradient-to-br from-cyan-950/50 to-slate-900 p-5">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-cyan-500" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Primary Path</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm font-medium tracking-tight text-slate-200">Create prompt &rarr; run CSV &rarr; evaluate results</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <aside class="space-y-4">
    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900">
      <div class="border-b border-slate-800 px-5 py-4">
        <p class="text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-cyan-400" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Smoke Test Plan</p>
        <h2 class="mt-2 text-lg font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-100" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">What to click first</h2>
      </div>
      <ol class="space-y-3 px-5 py-5 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-400">
        <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-200">1.</span> Open the engine UI and inspect the seeded prompt.</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-200">2.</span> Open the seeded draft test run and verify the CSV is visible.</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-200">3.</span> Add a provider API key and run the batch.</li>
        <li><span class="font-medium text-slate-200">4.</span> Evaluate results and inspect sorting, filtering, and detail pages.</li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-amber-900/40 bg-amber-950/30 p-5">
      <p class="text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-amber-500" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Provider Setup</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-400">
        Configure a provider key in
        <code class="rounded bg-slate-900 px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[11px] text-cyan-400 border border-slate-800" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">config/initializers/completion_kit.rb</code>
        or via environment variables before running a batch.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="rounded-lg border border-slate-800 bg-slate-900 p-5">
      <p class="text-[10px] font-medium uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-slate-600" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Seeded Fixture</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-base font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-200" style="font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;">Support Ticket Summarizer</p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm leading-7 text-slate-400">
        The seeded run uses two realistic support-ticket examples so you can validate the full flow without creating data by hand.
      </p>
    </div>
  </aside>
</section>
